            <p>You're not providing nearly enough information here for me to work with. The argument to your "setUseExternal" looks a lot like a local path, and I'm failing to see how that's different than simply providing a local path to Dojo in the helper.</p>

<p>Additionally, there are much better mechanisms for speeding up dojo: custom builds and CDNs. Custom builds intern all specified Dojo modules into a single file, including all templates, strips whitespace, and performs minification heuristics to ensure the smallest payload possible to the client. Pointing to a CDN is useful, as it allows your browser to use caches it already has in order to load the required functionality.</p>

